{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01KfiFB75csQhJsP4TCy2Kgn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is deployed and verified. Done.\n\n## Summary\n\nA 3-member authenticated MongoDB replica set is now running in the `mongodb` namespace.\n\n**What was created:**\n- **StatefulSet `mongodb-replica`** — 3 pods `mongodb-replica-0..2` (all `Running`, `3/3` ready), running `mongod --replSet mongodb-replica --keyFile ... --bind_ip_all`.\n- **Headless Service `mongodb-replica-svc`** — `clusterIP: None`, governing the StatefulSet so members resolve at `mongodb-replica-<n>.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`.\n- **Replica set `mongodb-replica`** — initiated with that exact `_id` (not the `rs0` default), members addressed by their stable DNS names. Status: **1 PRIMARY + 2 SECONDARY**.\n- **Keyfile auth** — a random 1024-byte keyfile stored in Secret `mongodb-keyfile`; an initContainer copies it into an emptyDir with `chmod 400` / `chown 999:999` so mongod accepts it for internal replica-set authentication.\n- **Users** (created via the localhost exception, then admin-authenticated):\n  - `admin-user` / `admin123password` (root on `admin`)\n  - `app-user` / `app123password` (readWrite on `appdb`)\n- **Secrets** holding the passwords under key `password`: `admin-user-password`, `app-user-password`.\n\n**Verification:**\n- Replica set healthy (PRIMARY + 2 SECONDARY, set name `mongodb-replica`).\n- As `app-user`, inserted a document into `appdb.items` and read it back (count = 1).\n- Confirmed the write replicated — reading from secondary `mongodb-replica-1` also returns count = 1.\n\nNo operators/CRDs were used."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":805,"cache_read_input_tokens":34775,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":805},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference